‚çù ]Git Log {Params}
‚çù
‚çù   - Show all commits for this repo (just like the "git log" Windows
‚çù     command).  Result looks like:
‚çù
‚çù       commit f62bf37965f12c76869a63b6771725c5b5aa4f01 (HEAD -> master, GitDemo/master)
‚çù       Author: Ian MacGregor <ian@zarkapl.com>
‚çù       Date:   Wed Jul 9 14:34:32 2025 -0400
‚çù
‚çù           Added a bad comment
‚çù
‚çù       commit 948cd33b19cdad08c0ff8527ef6a4fa3b9042053
‚çù       Author: Ian MacGregor <ian@zarkapl.com>
‚çù       Date:   Wed Jul 9 14:28:19 2025 -0400
‚çù
‚çù           first commit adding a function and a variable
‚çù
‚çù   - If {Params} is passed, it should be a string to pass to the
‚çù     command line after "git log ". E.g. to see the history of a
‚çù     specific file in the repo, you would pass "--follow [filename]"
‚çù     which would execute "git log --follow [filename]" to show the
‚çù     history of a specific file.
‚çù
‚çù   - [TLDR: Show history of a repo or file]

‚çù Syntax: R‚Üê‚çôGitLog PARAMS TEMP PDIR
‚çù PARAMS: Optional additional cvec to pass to "git log" command
‚çù   TEMP: Temp dir for use by ‚çôCOMMAND
‚çù   PDIR: WS' parent dir
 (RA TEMP PDIR)‚ÜêRA
‚çù "git log" : Show repo history
‚çù "git log --follow [filename]" : show file history
‚çù "git log branchB..branchA" : show commits in branchA not in branchB
